description.narrative: Output 1.3 Adolescent Health: Regional and national stakeholders have the evidence, guidance and multisectoral platforms to develop, implement and monitor policies and programmes to address the most prevalent adolescent health issues, including the prevention of HIV, NCDs, nutrition, mental health and adolescent pregnancies.,which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Hiv Prevention, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: OUTCOME 1: Girls, boys and adolescents in LAC benefit from equitable policies and programmes to guarantee their health, wellbeing and full development.
